[MK] case called at 1:24pm  
Defendant Chakayla M. Straham appears via videoconferencing from the Jefferson County Jail, in custody, along with Attorney Karl Huebner.  Public Service Special Prosecutor Melanie Flint appears in court for the State of Wisconsin. 
Attorney Flint verifies victim rights compliance. 
The Court finds that the video-connection is sight and sound sufficient. 
The Court verifies with Ms. Straham that she understands she has the right to be present in the courtroom for sentencing, and she is waiving this right.  
Maximum penalties are recited; Constitutional rights are reviewed; plea of " No Contest" is entered; factual basis stipulated.  The Court accepts the plea, finds the Defendant guilty, and orders Judgment of Conviction entered.

The Court withholds sentence and places Ms. Straham on Probation for one year, with conditions:
--to undergo AODA assessment and follow through with recommended treatment
--to undergo any other assessment, treatment, or counseling 
--to enroll/engage/complete a Criminal Thinking course of some kind (for example: Thinking for a Change) 
--to attempt to obtain/maintain employment and/or education program per Agent
--no possession of controlled substances without a valid prescription
--to comply with DNA sample provision 

The Court sets restitution at $0. 
Separate from the conditions of Probation, the Court orders payment of costs, fees and surcharges through the Clerk of Courts Office. [Clerk calculates this total to be: $453] The Court grants the Defendant sixty days to either pay the amount in full or to establish a payment plan with the Clerk of Courts Office.  Non-payment will result in 10 days in Jail.

Days credit for time already served:  5 days
recess 1:36pm
